[RETOREE]
Meh.

248
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:36,041
I don't really
like crowds, anyway.

249
00:10:36,125 --> 00:10:39,666
[CYAN]
Retoree! Here! Have one!

250
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:42,541
Uh-- Thanks a lot.

251
00:10:42,625 --> 00:10:44,291
Is something the matter?

252
00:10:44,375 --> 00:10:47,500
[RETOREE]
Mm-mm. Nah, nothin' at all.

253
00:10:47,583 --> 00:10:49,250
Okay. Guess that's good to hear.

254
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:52,541
As for me, I'm actually
a little down.

255
00:10:52,625 --> 00:10:53,791
[RETOREE]
Hm?

256
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:55,916
I'm not what you would
call a "strong swimmer,"

257
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,625
or even very good at
sports in general.

258
00:10:58,708 --> 00:11:00,333
So I'm kinda worried
that I'll end up

259
00:11:00,416 --> 00:11:03,250
causing trouble for everyone.

260
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:04,708
But you know what they say,

261
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:08,375
"You're a meanie if you
don't participate," right?

262
00:11:08,458 --> 00:11:09,375
I believe it's

263
00:11:09,458 --> 00:11:11,458
"There's meaning
in participation."

264
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:13,333
[gasps]

265
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:18,333
[CYAN] But I think it's good
to challenge yourself.

266
00:11:18,416 --> 00:11:20,250
You shouldn't run away
from things just because

267
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:21,666
you're not the best at them.

268
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,458
It's okay to mess up!

269
00:11:23,541 --> 00:11:25,791
That's the best way to
learn how to get better!

270
00:11:25,875 --> 00:11:28,125
Let's have fun!

271
00:11:28,208 --> 00:11:29,875
Sounds good.

272
00:11:29,958 --> 00:11:32,750
You two are so
inspirational, pyuru!

273
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:33,958
Now don't forget.

274
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:36,083
Getting a cramp can
really slow you down.

275
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:37,791
So make sure to
warm up carefully

276
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:39,208
and do your best!

277
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:42,791
[RETOREE]
I'm fine as long as

278
00:11:42,875 --> 00:11:45,291
I'm with everyone from Plasma.

279
00:11:45,375 --> 00:11:47,375
That's enough for me.


280
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,000
[EMCEE 4A]
Okay!


281
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:53,916
Are all our contestants
warmed up and ready to go?


282
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:57,791
It's time to start the games
you've all been waiting for!

283
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:08,583
♪

284
00:12:16,583 --> 00:12:18,875
[SHUZO] ♪ I'm running through
a boiling highway ♪

285
00:12:18,958 --> 00:12:22,083
♪ Between the ocean waves ♪

286
00:12:22,166 --> 00:12:25,666
♪ It's reflection seems
so close to me ♪

287
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:29,250
♪ It's lights up in the
night like Star Shine ♪

288
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:31,666
♪ I always felt like
I could reach out ♪

289
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:35,291
♪ And I could touch
the "Sky so high!" ♪

290
00:12:35,375 --> 00:12:38,083
I'm getting the hang of this!

291
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:39,750
[yelps]

292
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:41,000
[EMCEE 4A]
Oh!

293
00:12:41,083 --> 00:12:42,791
Contestant Chuchu has
fallen into the water!

294
00:12:42,875 --> 00:12:44,166
I did it!

295
00:12:44,250 --> 00:12:47,000
[EMCEE 4A] Contestant Candy
Lapin reaches the goal!

296
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:49,500
[CHUCHU]
Oh, now I've gone and done it!

297
00:12:49,583 --> 00:12:51,875
[whistle blows]

298
00:12:51,958 --> 00:12:54,208
Here I go, pyuru!

299
00:12:54,291 --> 00:12:55,916
One... Two...

300
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,125
Pyuru!

301
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:59,916
[yelps] P-P-Pyuru!

302
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,791
Looks like I win!

303
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:04,875
[EMCEE 4A]
Up next is the water rodeo!

304
00:13:04,958 --> 00:13:07,291
Whoever can stand the water
coming from all directions

305
00:13:07,375 --> 00:13:08,750
the longest wins!

306
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:10,125
All right.

307
00:13:10,208 --> 00:13:10,958
[EMCEE 4A]
Ready?

308
00:13:11,041 --> 00:13:13,666
Huh? Meow?

309
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:17,208
[EMCEE 4A laughs]
Contestant Cyan has fallen off!

310
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:19,458
The event hasn't
even started yet!

311
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:24,750
I can't get them in at all!

312
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:32,000
Like, oh, my gosh!

313
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:33,791
You're amazing, Rosia!

314
00:13:39,708 --> 00:13:41,708
Ah... This is just
the beginning!

315
00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:43,666
I will never give up!

316
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:51,666
[CHUCHU, CYAN, MOA cheering]

317
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:56,833
You're so close! You can
do it! Come on! Come on!

318
00:14:05,208 --> 00:14:06,833
[RETOREE]
A chicken fight with teammates

319
00:14:06,916 --> 00:14:08,458
I don't really know.

320
00:14:08,541 --> 00:14:11,958
And the one I do know
is that lame Rosia.

321
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:13,666
I wish I could've been
on the same team

322
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:15,125
as Cyan and the others.

323
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:17,708
[STAFF 4A]
On your right! Coming through!

324
00:14:17,791 --> 00:14:19,166
Excuse us, please!

325
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:19,916
[STAFF 4B]
Excuse us!

326
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,500
[STAFF 4C]
Excuse us!

327
00:14:22,541 --> 00:14:24,791
[STAFF 4A] Aw, man!
It won't fit through the door!

328
00:14:24,875 --> 00:14:26,125
[STAFF 4B]
What if we flip it upright?

329
00:14:26,208 --> 00:14:28,375
Maybe I'll just sit it out.

330
00:14:32,208 --> 00:14:33,666
[ROSIA]
Hm...

331
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:37,375
[ROSIA]
All right! Scoot, scoot, scoot!

332
00:14:37,458 --> 00:14:39,291
Left, right!

333
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,833
[sighs]

334
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:44,375
[gasps]

335
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:45,500
[gasps]

336
00:14:45,583 --> 00:14:48,500
Hey, Retoree! Whoa,
you surprised me!

337
00:14:48,583 --> 00:14:50,625
Why are you hanging out
in a place like this?

338
00:14:50,708 --> 00:14:53,958
[RETOREE]
N-No reason. I was just leaving.

339
00:14:54,041 --> 00:14:55,833
What did you come here for?

340
00:14:55,916 --> 00:14:59,416
I, uh, you know just came
to look for something I forgot!

341
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:02,333
Oh, my! I wonder
where it could be!

342
00:15:02,416 --> 00:15:06,125
Maybe here? Or over here?

343
00:15:06,208 --> 00:15:07,333
--Under here?
--[RETOREE] Well, I'm out.

344
00:15:07,416 --> 00:15:08,791
--Under here?
--See ya.

345
00:15:11,416 --> 00:15:12,541
[door rattles]

346
00:15:12,625 --> 00:15:15,250
[RETOREE]
Huh?

347
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:17,375
Ugh. What are you
doing over there?

348
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,125
The door. It won't open!

349
00:15:19,208 --> 00:15:20,750
What?

350
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:21,875
--[ROSIA] Sure.
--[RETOREE] See?

351
00:15:21,958 --> 00:15:23,458
You're kidding, right?

352
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:29,041
[ROSIA]
What the--?

353
00:15:29,125 --> 00:15:31,375
No way! Why won't it open?

354
00:15:31,458 --> 00:15:32,625
[ANNOUNCER]
Attention all contestants!

355
00:15:32,708 --> 00:15:34,291
Attention all contestants!

356
00:15:34,375 --> 00:15:35,458
Everyone in the chicken fight:

357
00:15:35,541 --> 00:15:37,125
please gather by the
pool in 15 minutes!

358
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:39,083
We have to hurry!

359
00:15:39,166 --> 00:15:42,583
[ROSIA grunting] Come on,
please! Open, open, open...

360
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:45,833
[RETOREE] Oh, well.
Maybe it's for the best.

361
00:15:45,916 --> 00:15:47,250
If we're stuck in here,

362
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:50,916
then I won't have to be
in the chicken fight.

363
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,291
[EMCEE 4A]
Now!

364
00:15:52,375 --> 00:15:54,166
It's time for the second
heat of the freestyle race!

365
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:57,416
Keep a close eye on contestants
Corriente and Jacklyn!

366
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,208
They're both
exceptional swimmers!

367
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:00,416
We're expecting an event record!

368
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:01,958
Good luck, girl.
You're gonna need it.

369
00:16:02,041 --> 00:16:02,791
[EMCEE 4A]
On your mark.

370
00:16:02,875 --> 00:16:04,541
That's what you think.

371
00:16:13,791 --> 00:16:15,333
[JACKLYN]
Almost!

372
00:16:19,416 --> 00:16:20,708
Yeah! I did it!

373
00:16:20,791 --> 00:16:24,541
[EMCEE 4A] There it is!
The fastest time in history!

374
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:28,375
That's how it's done! Boo-yah!

375
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:29,875
[EMCEE 4A]
Results for the second heat

376
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:33,166
of the freestyle race are:
1st place, Contestant Jacklyn.

377
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:35,416
2nd place, Contestant Corriente.

378
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,541
These two have broken
the event record!

379
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:40,083
Congratulations to them both!

380
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:42,958
Hey, Retoree.

381
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,375
It's real talk time.

382
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:49,666
You look super uncomfortable
when I get close to Cyan.

383
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:54,291
That's just... It's whatever.

384
00:16:54,375 --> 00:16:56,833
Well, there's no need
to worry, either way.

385
00:16:56,916 --> 00:16:58,833
I mean, it's not like
I like-like her

386
00:16:58,916 --> 00:17:00,166
or anything like that.

387
00:17:00,250 --> 00:17:02,458
I'm fascinated by her talent!

388
00:17:04,041 --> 00:17:07,125
Her talent?

389
00:17:07,208 --> 00:17:08,875
Because she's the
first person I've met

390
00:17:08,958 --> 00:17:11,208
that I didn't wanna lose to.

391
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:14,000
[ROSIA]
Until she came along,

392
00:17:14,083 --> 00:17:17,500
I was able to get the results
I wanted by working hard.

393
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:20,333
I had never lost
to anyone before.

394
00:17:20,416 --> 00:17:23,708
It was my first time
to ever feel that way.

395
00:17:23,791 --> 00:17:26,458
That's why I'm
interested in Cyan.

396
00:17:29,666 --> 00:17:31,916
Listen, you might not
think winning or losing

397
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,041
really matters all that much.

398
00:17:34,125 --> 00:17:35,541
But to me, it does!

399
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:37,708
Working hard and doing
all that I can help

400
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:40,416
make my music be
the best it can be!

401
00:17:42,125 --> 00:17:45,250
[HOLMY]
Jacklyn, that was incredible!

402
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:46,833
It was really close, though!

403
00:17:46,916 --> 00:17:49,833
I bet This swimsuit Rosia gave
me probably helped me win!

404
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:53,666
Huh? Oh, yeah.
Where is Rosia, anyway?

405
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:55,333
Retoree's missing, too.

406
00:17:55,416 --> 00:17:56,250
[CHUCHU, CYAN]
What?

407
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:59,166
I wonder what happened to them.

408
00:17:59,250 --> 00:18:00,041
[ROSIA]
There you have it.

409
00:18:00,125 --> 00:18:02,166
That's why I wanna win.

410
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:05,833
That's what interests
me about Cyan.

411
00:18:05,916 --> 00:18:09,500
[RETOREE] She's not really the
person I imagined her to be.

412
00:18:09,583 --> 00:18:12,208
Up until now, I didn't
really like her.

413
00:18:12,291 --> 00:18:13,750
It's okay to mess up!

414
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:16,583
That's the best way to
learn how to get better!

415
00:18:16,666 --> 00:18:18,375
Let's have fun!

416
00:18:24,541 --> 00:18:25,583
Listen.

417
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:27,833
I think I might've
had the wrong idea.

418
00:18:27,916 --> 00:18:29,666
[ROSIA]
Huh?

419
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:32,375
About the swim meet
today, for one thing.

420
00:18:32,458 --> 00:18:36,083
Because of all the crowds,
I decided from the start

421
00:18:36,166 --> 00:18:39,375
that I wasn't gonna
have any fun.

422
00:18:39,458 --> 00:18:41,000
Also...

423
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:47,083
Don't we have a chicken fight?

424
00:18:47,166 --> 00:18:49,500
We sure do!

425
00:18:49,583 --> 00:18:50,666
But if we're gonna make it,

426
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:53,291
we've totes gotta get
out of this place.

427
00:18:53,375 --> 00:18:56,041
[EMCEE 4A] It's time for the
last event: the chicken fight!

428
00:18:56,125 --> 00:18:58,125
The red team has an
advantage, but the team

429
00:18:58,208 --> 00:19:00,208
who wins the chicken
fight will receive

430
00:19:00,291 --> 00:19:04,333
a rockin' 690,000 points!

431
00:19:04,416 --> 00:19:07,291
What about all the points we got
from everything up until now?

432
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:09,166
Not much point in competing.

433
00:19:09,250 --> 00:19:12,125
Seems like this always happens.

434
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:15,708
[RETOREE]
I-It's not open yet? Seriously?

435
00:19:15,791 --> 00:19:18,500
[ROSIA] I know, right?
The window's stuck!

436
00:19:18,583 --> 00:19:21,333
I'm lighter than you, so just
keep holding me up, okay?

437
00:19:21,416 --> 00:19:24,416
[RETOREE] She always says
just a little too much.

438
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,125
[gasps, yelps] 

439
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:29,500
[BOTH yelping]

440
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:33,458
[BOTH groaning]

441
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:35,666
[CHUCHU] Retoree! Rosia!
You're here, too?

442
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:36,541
Thank goodness!

443
00:19:36,625 --> 00:19:38,416
We looked for you everywhere!

444
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:41,250
We were worried, pyuru!

445
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:42,458
Sorry.

446
00:19:42,541 --> 00:19:43,458
Rosia!

447
00:19:43,541 --> 00:19:45,000
I'm so glad we found you!

448
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:46,583
What were you doing?

449
00:19:46,666 --> 00:19:48,291
Yeah. You missed the race.

450
00:19:48,375 --> 00:19:50,166
[ROSIA]
Sorry that I worried you.

451
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:52,791
but we don't have any time
to just stand around. 

452
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:55,291
The white team, led by Rosia,

453
00:19:55,375 --> 00:20:01,000
will definitely not lose! Right?

454
00:20:01,083 --> 00:20:03,041
[ROSIA]
Gooo!

455
00:20:03,125 --> 00:20:04,416
[gunshot]

456
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:11,666
[yelps]

457
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:14,166
All right!

458
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:20,625
Look out. This one is all ours!

459
00:20:20,708 --> 00:20:23,208
Oh, no you don't!

460
00:20:23,291 --> 00:20:25,416
That's not gonna work on me!

461
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:26,625
So not fair

462
00:20:26,708 --> 00:20:28,791
Now it's my turn!

463
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:35,583
[gasps] Counterattack!

464
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:36,875
Okay!

465
00:20:36,958 --> 00:20:39,541
[yells]

466
00:20:39,625 --> 00:20:41,166
I've been bested!

467
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:43,875
We did it!

468
00:20:43,958 --> 00:20:45,708
That was a cool move, Retoree!

469
00:20:45,791 --> 00:20:47,000
Great idea!

470
00:20:47,083 --> 00:20:48,416
Yeah, it was!

471
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:49,500
[EMCEE 4A]
That's it!

472
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:51,875
The last team remaining
is Holmy, Wendy,

473
00:20:51,958 --> 00:20:54,041
Retoree and Rosia!

474
00:20:54,125 --> 00:20:55,625
Yay! We won!

475
00:20:55,708 --> 00:20:58,791
[EMCEE 4A] And that gives
the white team 690,000,

476
00:20:58,875 --> 00:21:02,333
bringing their total to 690,180!

477
00:21:02,416 --> 00:21:04,708
The white team wins!

478
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:06,583
Yes! Retoree!

479
00:21:12,458 --> 00:21:13,625
[ROSIA, RETROEE]
Hmph.

480
00:21:13,708 --> 00:21:16,125
[CYAN]
Retoree!

481
00:21:16,208 --> 00:21:17,583
[yelps]

482
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:19,000
[CHUCHU, CYAN, MOA, TSUKINO,
HOLMY, JACKLYN] We did it!

483
00:21:22,958 --> 00:21:25,125
Retoree, you were
absolutely amazing!

484
00:21:25,208 --> 00:21:27,750
You and Rosia worked
great together, pyuru!

485
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,375
It's all thanks to Cyan.

486
00:21:29,458 --> 00:21:31,625
Huh? To me?

487
00:21:31,708 --> 00:21:33,458
Did I do something?

488
00:21:33,541 --> 00:21:36,083
[RETOREE chuckles]

489
00:21:36,166 --> 00:21:38,875
[TSUKINO, ROSIA, JACKLYN, HOLMY
laughing, chattering]

490
00:21:38,958 --> 00:21:40,041
Oh?

491
00:21:51,416 --> 00:21:53,833
[SHIBARIN] Y'all! We're
never gonna make it!

492
00:21:53,916 --> 00:21:56,583
[KITTSUN] That old guy hates
it when we're late, too!

493
00:21:56,666 --> 00:21:58,291
[POKOE]
We have to hurry!

494
00:21:58,375 --> 00:21:59,833
[HAKKUN]
I hope he's not there yet.

495
00:21:59,916 --> 00:22:01,416
[SHIBARIN]
That's wishful thinkin'.

496
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,500
[KITTSUN]
Right?

497
00:22:02,583 --> 00:22:04,125
Like he's got
anything better to do.

498
00:22:04,208 --> 00:22:05,375
[POKOE]
Let's step on it!

499
00:22:05,458 --> 00:22:08,541
[HAKKUN] Yeah, he's scary
when he gets mad!

